## 1. Status Partition (Score 12.5) — TLP-style

**Relation:** For any set of issues, `list(status=open) ∪ list(status=in_progress) ∪ list(status=closed) ∪ list(status=deferred) ∪ list(status=draft) ∪ list(status=blocked) ∪ list(status=tombstone) ∪ list(status=pinned) == list(all)`

**Bug classes caught:** Missing status variants in SQL filters, off-by-one in status enum matching, shadow statuses falling through to wrong partition.

**File:** tests/proptest_status_partition.rs

```rust
proptest! {
    #[test]
    fn status_partition_is_exhaustive(issues in prop::collection::vec(arb_issue(), 1..20)) {
        let storage = populate_storage(&issues);
        let all = storage.list_issues(&ListFilters { all: true, ..Default::default() })?;
        let mut partitioned = BTreeSet::new();
        for status in &["open","in_progress","closed","deferred","draft","blocked","tombstone","pinned"] {
            let subset = storage.list_issues(&ListFilters {
                status: vec![status.to_string()],
                all: true,
                ..Default::default()
            })?;
            for issue in &subset {
                prop_assert!(partitioned.insert(issue.id.clone()),
                    "Issue {} appeared in multiple status partitions", issue.id);
            }
        }
        prop_assert_eq!(partitioned.len(), all.len(),
            "Status partition count {} != list(all) count {}", partitioned.len(), all.len());
    }
}
```

## 2. Claim Exclusion (Score 10.0) — State Transition

**Relation:** If x is in `ready()` and we `claim(x, actor)`, then x must NOT appear in subsequent `ready()` results (because claim sets status=in_progress or assignee!=null).

**Bug classes caught:** Ready filter not excluding in_progress, assignee filter bypass, cache staleness after claim.

**File:** tests/proptest_claim_exclusion.rs

```rust
proptest! {
    #[test]
    fn claimed_issue_not_in_ready(
        title in "[A-Za-z][A-Za-z0-9 ]{1,40}",
        actor in "[a-z]{3,10}",
    ) {
        let storage = setup_with_open_issue(&title);
        let ready_before = storage.get_ready_issues(&ReadyFilters::default(), ReadySortPolicy::Priority)?;
        prop_assert!(!ready_before.is_empty());

        storage.update_issue(&issue_id, &IssueUpdate {
            status: Some(Status::InProgress),
            assignee: Some(Some(actor)),
            claim_actor: Some(actor.clone()),
            ..Default::default()
        }, "proptest")?;

        let ready_after = storage.get_ready_issues(&ReadyFilters::default(), ReadySortPolicy::Priority)?;
        prop_assert!(ready_after.iter().all(|i| i.id != issue_id),
            "Claimed issue {} still in ready list", issue_id);
    }
}
```

## 3. Idempotent Re-Import (Score 8.0) — Equivalence

**Relation:** `state(import(import(jsonl))) == state(import(jsonl))` — importing the same JSONL file twice produces identical database state.

**Bug classes caught:** Duplicate insert errors, content_hash drift on re-import, comment/label/dep duplication.

**File:** tests/proptest_idempotent_import.rs

```rust
